cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL 

This paper deals with typechecking in programming languages, specifically with intersection and union types. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and completeness, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses techniques for reducing the number of choices in typechecking, which could fall under cs.TL (Type Theory and Logic) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper deals with soundness in a call-by-value semantics, which could relate to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
